Tutorial for discovering drug targets via network analysis

Mario Arrieta-Ortiz (Institute for Systems Biology, Baliga Lab)

March 25, 2019

  1. Loading required libraries
require('ggplot2')
require('miscTools')
require('synergyfinder')
  1. Plot effect of BDQ in MTB growth
# Load growth data
survival_data<-read.csv("data/wt_survival.csv")
treatment<-factor(survival_data$BDQ)
ggplot(survival_data,aes(x=Time, y=cfu_log10, col=treatment)) + 
  geom_line(aes(linetype=factor(treatment)),show.legend = F) +
  geom_point(aes(color=factor(treatment)), size=2) + xlab("Time (h)") + ylab("Log10 CFU/mL")

  1. Identify differentially expressed genes in response to BDQ treatment and evaluate functional enrichment
# Load results of differential expression analysis for BDQ treatment (Peterson et al, 2016; GEO accession:GSE72459)
bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output = read.csv('data/BDQ.genes.ttest.p.value.ALL.csv', header = T, row.names = 1)
# Preview the loaded table
print(bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output[1:3,])
# Create volcano plot 
# Define p-value threshold
pv_threshold = 0.01
# Define fold change threshold
fc_threshold = 1.5
plot(bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output[,"FC"], -log10(bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output[,"p.value"]), col = rgb(0,0,1,0.25), pch = 20,main = 'Differential expression in BDQ treatment', ylab = '-log10(p-value)', xlab = 'log2(Fold-Change)')
abline(h = -log10(pv_threshold), col = rgb(1,0,0,0.5), lwd = 2,lty=2)
abline(v=c(-fc_threshold, fc_threshold), col = rgb(1,0,0,0.5),lwd = 2,lty=2)

# Define set of differentially expressed genes
DE_genes = rownames(bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output)[which(abs(bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output[,"FC"])>=fc_threshold & bdq_diff_exp_analysis_output[,"p.value"]<=pv_threshold)]
print(paste("There are",length(DE_genes), "DEGs",sep=" "))
[1] "There are 773 DEGs"
# Load MTB genome annotation from Tuberculist database
mtb.annotation = read.csv('data/full_annotation.csv', header = T)
# Preview annotation table
print(mtb.annotation[1:5,])
annotation.categories = unique(mtb.annotation[,2])
#Save the genes associated with each category
categories_membership = list()
for(t in annotation.categories) {
    categories_membership[[t]] = mtb.annotation$Gene[mtb.annotation$Annotation==t]
}
# Perform hypergeometric test to detect functional enrichment in the set of differentially expressed genes
de_func_enrich = rep(1, length(annotation.categories))
names(de_func_enrich)<-annotation.categories
for(i in 1:length(annotation.categories)) {
    current_category = categories_membership[[i]]
    # Number of successes
    q = length(intersect(current_category, DE_genes))
    # Number of potential sucesses
    m = length(current_category)
    # Sample size
    k = length(DE_genes)
    # Number of potential failures
    n = 3999-m
    if(q>0) {
        de_func_enrich[i] = phyper(q, m, n, k, lower.tail = F)
    }
}
as.matrix(de_func_enrich)

  1. Identify MTBs biclusters that are enriched with genes differentially expressed in BDQ treatment
# Load MTB biclusters (Peterson et al 2014, NAR)
biclust_genes = read.csv('data/bicluster.genes.csv', header = T, row.names = 1)
biclust_memb = list()
for(j in rownames(biclust_genes)) {
    biclust_memb[[j]] = strsplit(as.character(biclust_genes[j,1]), split = ' ')[[1]]
}
# Load set of high quality biclusters (based on mean residual)
filtered_bics = read.csv('data/Filtered.bicluster.444.fullname.csv', header = F)[,1]
# Create table with information about enrichment of biclusters with differentially expressed genes
bdq_de_bic1 = matrix(nrow = length(biclust_memb), ncol = 5, dimnames = list(names(biclust_memb), c('q', 'm', 'n', 'k', 'p_value')))
for(x in names(biclust_memb)) {
    # Number of successes
    q = length(intersect(biclust_memb[[x]], DE_genes))
    # Number of potential sucesses
    m = length(biclust_memb[[x]])
    # Sample size
    k = length(DE_genes)
    # Number of potential failures
    n = 3922-m
    pv = NA
    if(q>0) {
        pv = phyper(q, m, n, k, lower.tail = F)
    }
    bdq_de_bic1[x,] = c(q, m, n, k, pv)
}
# Correcting for multiple hypotheses testing
bdq_de_bic1 = cbind(bdq_de_bic1, p_value.BH = p.adjust(bdq_de_bic1[,'p_value'], method = 'BH', n = nrow(bdq_de_bic1)))
# Select enriched biclusters with low mean residual
bdq_de_enrich_bics = intersect(rownames(bdq_de_bic1)[which(bdq_de_bic1[,'p_value.BH']<=0.05)], filtered_bics)

4.Check functional annotation of biclusters enriched with differentially expressed genes

enrich_bics_annotation = rep('No enrichment', length(bdq_de_enrich_bics))
for(u in 1:length(bdq_de_enrich_bics)) {
    current.bic = biclust_memb[[bdq_de_enrich_bics[u]]]
    enriched.cat = c()
    for(i in annotation.categories) {
        q = length(intersect(categories_membership[[i]], current.bic))
        m = length(categories_membership[[i]])
        k = length(current.bic)
        n = 3922-m
        if(q>0) {
            pval = phyper(q, m, n, k, lower.tail = F)
            if(pval < 0.01) {
                enriched.cat = append(enriched.cat,as.character(i))
            }
        }
    }
    if(length(enriched.cat)>0) {
        enrich_bics_annotation[u] = paste(enriched.cat,collapse = ';')
    }
}
enrich_bics_annotation = cbind(bdq_de_enrich_bics, enrich_bics_annotation)
colnames(enrich_bics_annotation)<-c("Bicluster","Enriched categories")
print(enrich_bics_annotation)

# Due to time constraint, we load the output of analysis comparing biclusters and regulons 
bicluster_tf_overlaps = read.csv('data/Bicluster.TF.Overlap.csv', header = T)
bicluster_tf_network = list()
for(i in 1:nrow(bicluster_tf_overlaps)) {
    bic1 = paste('biclust_', as.character(bicluster_tf_overlaps[i, 'Bicluster']), sep = '')
    if(!(bic1 %in% names(bicluster_tf_network))) {
        bicluster_tf_network[[bic1]] = c()
    }
    bicluster_tf_network[[bic1]] = c(bicluster_tf_network[[bic1]], as.character(bicluster_tf_overlaps[i, 'TF']))
}
print(bicluster_tf_network[intersect(bdq_de_enrich_bics, names(bicluster_tf_network))])

  1. Explore profile of selected biclusters during treatment with other compounds
# Load Drug expression data (this data was simulated to facilitate analysis)
drug1 = read.csv('data/drug_treated_expression.csv', header = T, row.names = 1)
print(drug1[1:3,1:9])
# We focus on biclusters enriched in detox/adaptation related genes 
# This category was selected because of its potential role in antibiotic tolerance
genes_435 = biclust_memb[['biclust_435']]
genes_452 = biclust_memb[['biclust_452']]
# Names and colors for each compound
tmpNames = gsub('\\.2', '', gsub('\\.1','',colnames(drug1)))
tmpNames2 = unlist(sapply(as.character(unique(tmpNames)), function(x) { c(x,rep('',sum(tmpNames==x)-1)) }))
cols = rep(rainbow(5),8)
tmpCols = unlist(sapply(1:36, function(x) { rep(cols[x],sum(tmpNames==unique(tmpNames)[x])) }))
# Plot expression of genes in bicluster 435 & bicluster 452
par(mar = c(7,4,4,2))
boxplot(drug1[genes_435,], las = 2, names = tmpNames2, main = 'Bicluster 435', ylab = 'Fold change', col = tmpCols)
abline(h = 0)

boxplot(drug1[genes_452,], las = 2, names = tmpNames2, main ='Bicluster 452', ylab = 'Fold change', col = tmpCols)
abline(h = 0)

  1. Select drug to sinergyze with BDQ
# Prioritize secondary drugs for bicluster 435
cm_435 = colMedians(drug1[genes_435,])
# T-test to compare expression of the cluster in each compound respect to BDQ treatment
t_435 = p.adjust(sapply(unique(tmpNames)[2:36], function(x) { t.test(cm_435[which(tmpNames==x)],cm_435[which(tmpNames=='Bedaquiline')])$p.value }),method='BH')
delta_fc_435 = sapply(unique(tmpNames)[2:36], function(x) { median(cm_435[which(tmpNames==x)])-median(cm_435[which(tmpNames=='Bedaquiline')]) })
plot(delta_fc_435, -log10(t_435),main='Bicluster 435',ylim=c(0,4.5),xlim=c(-5.5,5.5),col=tmpCols,pch=20)
abline(h=-log10(0.05),col=rgb(1,0,0,0.5))
abline(v=c(0))
drug_435 = unique(tmpNames)[intersect(which(fc_435==min(fc_435)),which(t_435<=0.05))+1]
points(fc_435[drug_435], -log10(t_435[drug_435]),col='red',pch=1,lwd=2)
text(fc_435[drug_435]+0.05, -log10(t_435[drug_435]),drug_435,pos=4,col=rgb(1,0,0,1))

# Prioritize secondary drugs for bicluster 452
cm_452 = colMeans(drug1[genes_452,])
t_452 = p.adjust(sapply(unique(tmpNames)[2:36], function(x) { t.test(cm_452[which(tmpNames==x)],cm_452[which(tmpNames=='Bedaquiline')])$p.value }),method='BH')
delta_fc_452 = sapply(unique(tmpNames)[2:36], function(x) { median(cm_452[which(tmpNames==x)])-median(cm_452[which(tmpNames=='Bedaquiline')]) })
plot(delta_fc_452, -log10(t_452),main='Bicluster 452',ylim=c(0,4.5),xlim=c(-5.5,5.5),col=tmpCols,pch=20)
abline(h=-log10(0.05),col=rgb(1,0,0,0.5))
abline(v=c(0))
drug_452 = unique(tmpNames)[intersect(which(fc_452==min(fc_452)),which(t_452<=0.05))+1]
points(fc_452[drug_452], -log10(t_452[drug_452]),col='red',pch=1,lwd=2)
text(fc_452[drug_452]-0.4, -log10(t_452[drug_452]),drug_452,pos=1,col=rgb(1,0,0,1))
